{"rendered": {"description": {"raw": "Don't use `__file__` to infer the location of the script - it is unreliable due to relative paths and the possibility of someone having called `os.chdir()`.\r\n\r\nAlso don't call `os.chdir()`, and use absolute paths for everything.\r\n\r\nI converted all the relative paths I knew about to absolute ones, and got all uses of `__file__`, but I may have missed some. Basic testing doesn't throw any file-not-found errors when running BLACS from a different directory.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Don't use <code>__file__</code> to infer the location of the script - it is unreliable due to relative paths and the possibility of someone having called <code>os.chdir()</code>.</p>\n<p>Also don't call <code>os.chdir()</code>, and use absolute paths for everything.</p>\n<p>I converted all the relative paths I knew about to absolute ones, and got all uses of <code>__file__</code>, but I may have missed some. Basic testing doesn't throw any file-not-found errors when running BLACS from a different directory.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "title": {"raw": "Absolute imports, and don't use __file__", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Absolute imports, and don't use <strong>file</strong></p>", "type": "rendered"}}, "type": "pullrequest", "description": "Don't use `__file__` to infer the location of the script - it is unreliable due to relative paths and the possibility of someone having called `os.chdir()`.\r\n\r\nAlso don't call `os.chdir()`, and use absolute paths for everything.\r\n\r\nI converted all the relative paths I knew about to absolute ones, and got all uses of `__file__`, but I may have missed some. Basic testing doesn't throw any file-not-found errors when running BLACS from a different directory.", "links": {"decline": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/labscript_suite/blacs/pullrequests/32/decline"}, "diffstat": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/labscript_suite/blacs/diffstat/labscript_suite